  <li id="comment-38974" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Laura</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/a-small-revolution/#comment-38974"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-26T17:31:32-05:00">Saturday, January 26, 2013 at 5:31 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>That essay by Zadie Smith really is something. I&#39;ve been recommending it around, too. </p>
<p>I knew it was going to be good when the second paragraph started like this: </p>
<p><i>&#8220;Perhaps the first thing to say is that I experience at least a little pleasure every day. I wonder if this is more than the usual amount? It was the same even in childhood when most people are miserable. I donâ€™t think this is because so many wonderful things happen to me but rather that the small things go a long way.&#8221;</i></p>
<p>That resonated with me. I assume it resonated with you, too, or you wouldn&#39;t have recommended. Feels so easy to be at a place where the small things give me pleasure, but since I haven&#39;t always been in this place, it also feels like a gift. </p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-38974' data-commentid="38974" data-postid="347" data-belowelement="comment-38974" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Laura" aria-label='Reply to Laura'>Reply</a>    </div>
  </li><!-- #comment-## -->
  <li id="comment-39096" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Laura</cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/a-small-revolution/#comment-39096"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-01-26T17:31:32-05:00">Saturday, January 26, 2013 at 5:31 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>That essay by Zadie Smith really is something. I&#39;ve been recommending it around, too. </p>
<p>I knew it was going to be good when the second paragraph started like this: </p>
<p><i>&#8220;Perhaps the first thing to say is that I experience at least a little pleasure every day. I wonder if this is more than the usual amount? It was the same even in childhood when most people are miserable. I donâ€™t think this is because so many wonderful things happen to me but rather that the small things go a long way.&#8221;</i></p>
<p>That resonated with me. I assume it resonated with you, too, or you wouldn&#39;t have recommended. Feels so easy to be at a place where the small things give me pleasure, but since I haven&#39;t always been in this place, it also feels like a gift. </p>
    </div>

