    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, I&#39;ve been following your blog all the way here in Pakistan for the past two years. When I read your post about post-partum depression, I felt your pain and I know exactly how debilitating it can be. I had my son last March and my depression didn&#39;t kick in until he was 6 months. I recently wrote about it on my food blog <a href="http://www.hungerandhawhai.com" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.hungerandhawhai.com</a>. I started the blog as a self-prescribed version of therapy and I&#39;d love for you to read the post. It&#39;s called, Motherhood: The Truth About Cats &#038; Blogs. I&#39;m hoping it&#39;ll offer some support and help you believe that there&#39;s light at the end of this tunnel. Take good care and I pray with all my heart that you pull through this soon!<a href="http://www.hungerandhawhai.com/2013/01/chickenpotpie.html" rel="nofollow ugc">http://www.hungerandhawhai.com/2013/01/chickenpotpie.html</a></p>
    </div>

