  <li id="comment-39188" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/07455777109778387077" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Brittany and Donny</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2013/01/a-small-revolution/#comment-39188"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2013-05-09T15:37:55-04:00">Thursday, May 9, 2013 at 3:37 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Hi Molly,<br />I just made these oatcakes for the millionth time since you posted the recipe.  This time, I used 50% rye flour and 50% whole wheat&#8230;and just like your rye crumble recipe, the nutty flavor of the rye flour made them even more unbelievable!  Yum!!!</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
